gomodel:SYNGO_4210  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure1, DLGAP2/SAPAP2 is enriched in the PSD fraction.\n\"For the comparative analysis of PSD fractions, equal protein amounts were analyzed by Western blotting with specific antibodies (Fig. 1, C and E).\nIn contrast, SAPAP1 and Shank3 levels were only elevated in neocortical PSD preparations, whereas SAPAP2, SAPAP3, and IRSp53 concentrations were selectively increased in hippocampal PSD fractions prepared from knockout animals.\n\n28/01/2021 Dnyanada: The paper does not comment on the specificity of the antibody used.. Experimental description: Biochemical preparation of PSDs from mouse brain\nLiteral form M&M\nBiochemical Cell Fractionation, Antibodies, and Western\nBlot Analysis-From mouse cortices and hippocampi, cytosolic, synaptosome, and PSD fractions were prepared as essentially described (25), snap-frozen in liquid nitrogen, and stored at -80 °C. Glutathione S-transferase fusion proteins containing amino acid residues 722-776, 636-699, and 694-747 of rat SAPAP1 (GenBankTM accession number NP_075235), SAPAP2 (P97837), and SAPAP3 (AAS90634) were used to raise and affinity-purify custom rabbit polyclonal antisera 5280, 5281, and 5269 (Pineda, Berlin, Germany), respectively." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4210" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

